      "text": [
        " قَالَ عَلِيٌّ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"لاَ بَأْسَ أَنْ يُسْلَفَ مَا يُوزَنُ فِيمَا يُكَالُ وَ مَا يُكَالُ فِيمَا يُوزَنُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3949 - Wahb ibn Wahb narrated from Ja'far ibn Muhammad from his father (as):\nImam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) said: \"There is no harm in advancing payment for what is weighed in exchange for what is measured, and for what is measured in exchange for what is weighed.\""
        ]
      }
